  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Cook the potatoes</strong></p>\n<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6. Boil a kettle.</p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>waxy</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into large bite-sized pieces.</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiling water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 15-20 minutes or until fork-tender.</p>\n<p>Once done, drain and set aside for later.</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1591.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1591.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1591.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1591.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1591.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Chop the garlic, shallot and sugar snaps</strong></p>\n<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong>.</p>\n<p>Peel and finely slice the<strong> shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>.</p>\n<p>Slice the<strong> sugar snap peas</strong> in half on a diagonal.</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1591.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1591.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1591.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1591.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1591.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Fry the pancetta</strong></p>\n<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat.</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>pancetta</strong> and cook for 5-6 minutes or until crispy.</p>\n<p>Once crispy, transfer the <strong>pancetta</strong> to a plate and return the pan to a medium heat.</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped shallot</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 2-3 minutes or until softened.</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1591.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1591.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1591.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1591.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1591.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Make the lemon vinaigrette</strong></p>\n<p>Meanwhile, re-boil half a kettle.</p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>little gem lettuce<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into wedges.</p>\n<p>Cut 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span> thin slices from the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>(make sure you save some for juicing!).</p>\n<p>Combine the <strong>juice</strong> of the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lemon</strong> in a bowl with the <strong>Dijon mustard</strong>, 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>– this is your<strong> lemon vinaigrette.</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
